Contracts with customers Satisfaction of perfurmance obligations

The Group is required to assess each of its contracts with customers to determine whether pen‘ormance obligations are satisfied over time or at a point in time in order to determine the appropriate method for recognising revenue. The Group has assessed that based on the contracts entered into with customers and the provisions of relevant iaws and regulations, the Group recognises revenue over time where contracts are entered into for property development (sale of properties to customers), the Group does not create an asset with an alternative use to the Group and has an enforceable right to payment for performance completed to date.
